
## 1. Overview
The Historical Records system tracks significant events, discoveries, and milestones in the game world. Records are created through specific triggers, stored efficiently, and displayed to players via various interfaces such as libraries, monuments, and player profiles. Designed to encourage long-term player legacy and world-building.

---

## 2. Data Schemas

### JSON Schema for Records

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "HistoricalRecord",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "record_id": { "type": "string" },
    "title": { "type": "string" },
    "description": { "type": "string" },
    "discovered_by": { "type": "string" },
    "date_discovered": { "type": "string", "format": "date" },
    "location": { "type": "string" },
    "category": { "type": "string" }, // e.g., "milestone", "discovery", "battle"
    "related_event": { "type": "string" }, // optional
    "media": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": { "type": "string" } // URLs or resource IDs for images/media
    }
  },
  "required": ["record_id", "title", "description", "discovered_by", "date_discovered"]
}
```

### Validation Rules
- `record_id`: unique string identifier.
- `title`: non-empty.
- `description`: detailed text.
- `discovered_by`: player name or ID.
- `date_discovered`: valid date string in ISO format.
- `category`: optional but useful for filtering.
- `media`: optional; can include images or video references.

